    <!-- Application Structure Plan:
         1. Dashboard Layout: Sidebar nav (desktop) / Bottom nav (mobile) to switch between 4 key views.
         2. View 1: "√úberblick & Fakten" (General Info) - Cards for quick stats.
         3. View 2: "Regionen & Highlights" (The Core) - Interactive split view. Select a region (Atacama/Patagonia/Central) to see specific itineraries/activities.
         4. View 3: "Klima & Reisezeit" (Data Viz) - Charts comparing temp/rain in Oct/Nov to help them visualize packing needs.
         5. View 4: "Logistik & Tipps" (Practical) - Transport flow and interactive packing checklist.
         Rationale: This structure breaks the complex logistics of a 4000km long country into manageable, bite-sized decision zones.
    -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         1. Weather Comparison (Bar Chart): Shows the drastic temp difference between Calama and Punta Arenas in Nov to emphasize packing layers.
         2. Cost/Budget Breakdown (Doughnut Chart): Visualizes where the money goes in a mid-range trip (Flights vs Tours vs Accommodation).
         3. Interactive Region Cards: Uses Unicode icons and CSS styling to represent environments (Desert vs Ice) without raster images.
         4. Transport Timeline: A vertical step-flow using CSS borders to show the logical route (Santiago -> North -> South).
         CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used.
    -->
